00:11:45.727 --> 00:11:46.895
<i>Okay.</i>

235
00:11:47.812 --> 00:11:49.022
<i>Um.</i>

236
00:11:49.898 --> 00:11:52.025
<i>I'd rather do it in person.
Uh. this is like my workplace.</i>

237
00:11:52.108 --> 00:11:54.694
- <i>Do you live near the city?</i>
- Uh…

238
00:11:54.777 --> 00:11:56.779
[whispering]
Say… Say. "I don't live in the city."

239
00:11:56.863 --> 00:11:58.239
Yes. yep.

240
00:11:58.323 --> 00:12:00.867
<i>Great. I'll send the address
to your account.</i>

241
00:12:00.950 --> 00:12:02.744
- Okay. Okay.
- <i>Okay.</i>

242
00:12:04.579 --> 00:12:06.122
Okay. [sighs]

243
00:12:06.623 --> 00:12:07.790
I didn't see the ring.

244
00:12:07.874 --> 00:12:10.877
- No. I didn't either.
- Are you really gonna go in person?

245
00:12:10.960 --> 00:12:12.462
[stammers] In person's kind of weird.

246
00:12:12.545 --> 00:12:14.339
I mean… [stammers]
…we don't have a choice.

247
00:12:14.964 --> 00:12:16.841
- [Geri] We?
- We're going.

248
00:12:17.508 --> 00:12:18.551
Cool.

249
00:12:19.302 --> 00:12:21.554
Paula's ex confirmed she had motive.

250
00:12:21.638 --> 00:12:23.681
The cam boy was harassing everyone
in her life.

251
00:12:23.765 --> 00:12:25.058
Yeah. she told me about that.

252
00:12:25.141 --> 00:12:26.726
She wasn't hiding it.

253
00:12:26.809 --> 00:12:29.312
This bank account she gave us is boring.

254
00:12:29.395 --> 00:12:30.980
I hate this paper trail shit.

255
00:12:31.064 --> 00:12:34.108
Boring paper trail shit leads to arrests.

256
00:12:34.192 --> 00:12:35.735
Yeah. yeah.

257
00:12:35.818 --> 00:12:38.404
What do you think of the Diamondbacks?

258
00:12:38.488 --> 00:12:41.491
I think anyone who cares about
a baseball team outside their hometown

259
00:12:41.574 --> 00:12:43.201
is probably a degenerate gambler.

260
00:12:44.744 --> 00:12:47.247
There is nothing degenerate
about my gambling.

261
00:12:47.330 --> 00:12:52.710
Our lives are defined by luck.
and anyone who ignores that is stupid.

262
00:12:52.794 --> 00:12:53.920
Mm-hmm.

263
00:12:54.003 --> 00:12:56.005
You've been mocking me
because I've been losing.

264
00:12:56.089 --> 00:12:58.341
but eventually
the tide is going to come back.

265
00:12:58.883 --> 00:13:03.763
And the real loss is not being in the game
when your luck finally turns.

266
00:13:04.931 --> 00:13:06.266
Okay. Aristotle.

267
00:13:07.058 --> 00:13:09.644
Hope the Diamondbacks
know your philosophy.

268
00:13:10.603 --> 00:13:12.105
I think I'll go with the Cubs.

269
00:13:13.565 --> 00:13:14.566
[scoffs]

270
00:13:18.778 --> 00:13:21.364
[Paula] Okay.
I was expecting a-a coffee shop.

271
00:13:21.447 --> 00:13:24.826
[Rudy] Yeah.
maybe we should go to a coffee shop

272
00:13:24.909 --> 00:13:27.245
'cause this looks like a horror movie.

273
00:13:27.328 --> 00:13:28.955
- Yeah. it'll be fine.
- [Rudy] Will it?

274
00:13:29.038 --> 00:13:31.499
A guy who clearly rouges his nips.
by the way.

275
00:13:31.583 --> 00:13:35.128
wants to meet in person
at an abandoned murder motel.

276
00:13:35.211 --> 00:13:37.922
- So…
- It'll be okay. It's the daytime.

277
00:13:38.006 --> 00:13:40.675
Right. 'cause no one gets killed
in the daytime.

278
00:13:40.758 --> 00:13:43.344
I-I-I mean. I have to do something.
I'm going in.

279
00:13:43.928 --> 00:13:45.096
Oh. wait. Hold on. Hey.

280
00:13:45.847 --> 00:13:47.932
Use this. It's dry shampoo.

281
00:13:48.016 --> 00:13:50.226
- What?
- [stammers] For if something goes wrong.

282
00:13:51.060 --> 00:13:53.688
I got it in my eyes once.
it actually really burns.

283
00:13:55.857 --> 00:13:59.527
If I'm not back in 30 minutes. call me.

284
00:13:59.611 --> 00:14:00.904
- Set an alarm.
- [Geri] Okay.

285
00:14:35.021 --> 00:14:36.397
[phone chimes]

286
00:14:53.873 --> 00:14:55.708
[electronic music playing on speakers]

287
00:14:55.792 --> 00:14:57.168
Salutations.

288
00:14:58.086 --> 00:15:00.046
I'm Sky. So cool to meet you.

289
00:15:00.129 --> 00:15:01.589
Me too. I'm-I'm Paula.

290
00:15:05.218 --> 00:15:06.636
[sighs]

291
00:15:11.140 --> 00:15:12.517
It's a work in progress.

292
00:15:12.600 --> 00:15:14.143
Me and Trevor bought the place
with a friend.

293
00:15:14.227 --> 00:15:16.813
We're going to turn it
into apartments for college kids.

294
00:15:16.896 --> 00:15:19.440
- Wow. that's a really great idea.
- I know.

295
00:15:19.524 --> 00:15:21.985
Trevor was my mentor
in sex work and real estate.

296
00:15:22.068 --> 00:15:23.987
It's an interesting combination.

297
00:15:24.070 --> 00:15:27.407
But… [sighs] …I'll never be able
to finish it without him.

298
00:15:27.991 --> 00:15:29.325
I can't believe he's gone.

299
00:15:30.368 --> 00:15:33.037
Yeah. I'm just trying to figure out
what happened.

300
00:15:33.121 --> 00:15:34.122
Me too.

301
00:15:34.205 --> 00:15:37.333
[chuckles] I mean. in the cam world.
you know a lot of people.

302
00:15:37.417 --> 00:15:41.129
but you don't really know them.
Everyone's just a username and an avatar.

303
00:15:41.212 --> 00:15:43.423
Everyone's anonymous except for us.

304
00:15:43.506 --> 00:15:44.549
People see us.

305
00:15:45.425 --> 00:15:46.509
That's scary.

306
00:15:47.927 --> 00:15:50.805
So you said you had some information
about Trevor's death?

307
00:15:50.889 --> 00:15:52.348
[suspenseful music playing]

308
00:15:52.432 --> 00:15:53.725
Tell me what you know.

309
00:15:55.101 --> 00:15:57.145
[Paula] I'm not gonna tell you
until I know what you know.

310
00:15:58.938 --> 00:16:00.356
[Sky breathes deeply] Right.

311
00:16:02.984 --> 00:16:07.280
You know I'm bored if I'm asking you this.
but. um. how's Vi?

312
00:16:07.363 --> 00:16:09.908
Oh. that is over. [sighs]

313
00:16:09.991 --> 00:16:11.659
- What?
- Yeah. I told her to move out.

314
00:16:12.368 --> 00:16:14.329
That's huge. Why didn't you say anything?

315
00:16:14.412 --> 00:16:17.165
Maybe because you mock me every time I do.

316
00:16:17.248 --> 00:16:20.543
It was a week ago.
It's… It's fine. I'm fine.

317
00:16:20.627 --> 00:16:22.587
I will not bug you about her anymore.

318
00:16:22.670 --> 00:16:27.717
Okay. Well. I'm sure you'll find
someone new to bug me about soon.

319
00:16:28.885 --> 00:16:31.179
Maybe in law school.

320
00:16:31.930 --> 00:16:35.058
- You really want to be a lawyer?
- Yeah. I think so.

321
00:16:35.141 --> 00:16:36.434
Which one's a lawyer again?

322
00:16:36.517 --> 00:16:38.394
- They clean teeth. right?
- [chuckles]

323
00:16:38.478 --> 00:16:40.563
I got my BA in linguistics.

324
00:16:40.647 --> 00:16:43.858
which my dad thinks was just.
like. a total waste of 300 grand.

325
00:16:43.942 --> 00:16:46.861
So. now I'm just trying to be realistic.
you know?

326
00:16:46.945 --> 00:16:48.988
Yeah. Hmm. I do.

327
00:16:49.072 --> 00:16:51.866
But. you know. you're really smart.
so. you'll get into a great law school.

328
00:16:52.450 --> 00:16:53.743
Thanks.

329
00:16:53.826 --> 00:16:55.745
My dad isn't the most supportive either.

330
00:16:55.828 --> 00:16:58.456
He's always like.
"You're wasting your time

331
00:16:58.540 --> 00:17:01.251
on this journalism crap. Ger-Bear.

332
00:17:01.334 --> 00:17:03.294
The news is all going to be AI anyway."

333
00:17:03.378 --> 00:17:05.213
Sorry. that's rough.

334
00:17:05.296 --> 00:17:06.548
Mmm.

335
00:17:07.173 --> 00:17:09.551
Although it's not exactly the same. right?

336
00:17:09.634 --> 00:17:11.135
- What do you mean?
- Well. I mean.

337
00:17:11.219 --> 00:17:13.846
linguistics is a classical field of study.

338
00:17:13.930 --> 00:17:15.598
It's a solid base for a lot of careers.

339
00:17:15.682 --> 00:17:20.395
Journalism's pretty much just. like.
a totally outdated. dying medium.

340
00:17:20.478 --> 00:17:22.437
I hope you fail the LSATs.

341
00:17:23.313 --> 00:17:26.401
Okay. good talk. Ger-Bear.

342
00:17:30.613 --> 00:17:33.700
[electronic music continues]

343
00:17:39.622 --> 00:17:40.999
You sure you don't want
something to drink?

344
00:17:41.082 --> 00:17:42.458
We have fizzy water too.

345
00:17:42.542 --> 00:17:43.877
And milk.

346
00:17:44.502 --> 00:17:46.087
It's weird they never made fizzy milk.

347
00:17:46.170 --> 00:17:47.422
No. no. no. I'm all good.

348
00:17:47.505 --> 00:17:49.173
So. okay…

349
00:17:49.257 --> 00:17:51.509
So what else did Trevor get into
besides camming?

350
00:17:51.593 --> 00:17:52.927
I don't really know anything.

351
00:17:53.011 --> 00:17:57.265
Like I told you. um. I know Trevor
was hanging out with different people.

352
00:17:57.348 --> 00:17:58.725
I didn't know 'em all.

353
00:17:58.808 --> 00:18:03.938
Uh. Trevor was very flexible.
both sexually and physically.

354
00:18:04.022 --> 00:18:05.481
which is why he was such a high earner.

355
00:18:05.565 --> 00:18:07.233
I mean. he had a way
of making people open up…

356
00:18:07.317 --> 00:18:08.693
[screaming]

357
00:18:08.776 --> 00:18:09.819
- [Paula] Trevor?
- <i>Help!</i>

358
00:18:09.903 --> 00:18:11.446
[distorted] He knew what he was doing.

359
00:18:11.529 --> 00:18:13.281
I mean. we were making
real strides on this...

360
00:18:15.450 --> 00:18:19.204
He had this. uh…
He had this. uh. way with people…

361
00:18:21.456 --> 00:18:23.708
[speaking Serbian] <i>Ko si ti?</i> [pants]

362
00:18:23.791 --> 00:18:26.127
- [distorted] …while he pleasured himself…
- It was you.

363
00:18:27.212 --> 00:18:29.255
You were the one
who attacked Trevor in that video.

364
00:18:29.839 --> 00:18:31.216
- What?
- Yeah… [stammers]

365
00:18:31.299 --> 00:18:34.052
…you're a lefty and you've got
the green eyes and the tooth.

366
00:18:34.135 --> 00:18:37.388
Like… [stammers] …I. like…
Where's your weird two finger ring?

367
00:18:37.472 --> 00:18:38.848
- It was fucking you.
- No. No. no. no.

368
00:18:38.932 --> 00:18:40.600
- Yes. it was.
- It's not what you think.

369
00:18:40.683 --> 00:18:42.727
I mean. yes. that was me. but it was fake.

370
00:18:42.810 --> 00:18:45.605
It was all a scam. I'd never hurt Trevor.
I'd never hurt anybody.

371
00:18:45.688 --> 00:18:48.274
- People got hurt.
- Well. I didn't kill him.

372
00:18:48.358 --> 00:18:49.776
What you saw was fake.

373
00:18:49.859 --> 00:18:51.069
It was set up.

374
00:18:51.152 --> 00:18:52.445
It was Trevor's idea.

375
00:18:52.529 --> 00:18:54.739
He had this whole plan
to shake down some clients

376
00:18:54.822 --> 00:18:57.450
with his "help me. I'm pretty
and in trouble" thing.

377
00:18:57.534 --> 00:19:00.453
We were just trying to get money.
Not that that's an excuse.

378
00:19:00.537 --> 00:19:02.705
I shouldn't have done it to you.
I shouldn't have done it to anybody.

379
00:19:02.789 --> 00:19:05.792
but now I just want to find out
who killed my friend.

380
00:19:07.126 --> 00:19:10.213
I'm gonna go look around.
Stay here in case Paula comes back.

381
00:19:10.296 --> 00:19:12.632
- I don't wanna be here alone. you know…
- Just lock the doors.

382
00:19:12.715 --> 00:19:16.594
And if anyone comes. just tell them
that boring story about your dad.

383
00:19:16.678 --> 00:19:18.304
Like. trust me. they'll leave.

384
00:19:24.143 --> 00:19:25.144
[Sky] Great.

385
00:19:25.228 --> 00:19:27.605
[stammers] Look.
it's probably somebody else we scammed.

386
00:19:27.689 --> 00:19:30.900
Fuck. I mean. it could be anybody.
a man. a woman.

387
00:19:30.984 --> 00:19:32.402
It was a man.

388
00:19:32.485 --> 00:19:35.113
- I mean. most likely. yeah.
- It was. it was a man.

389
00:19:35.196 --> 00:19:36.364
I saw it.

390
00:19:36.447 --> 00:19:37.657
I was hiding in the closet.

391
00:19:37.740 --> 00:19:40.159
I-I-I… [sighs]

392
00:19:40.243 --> 00:19:41.744
I saw that a man did it.

393
00:19:42.829 --> 00:19:44.706
You were there? [chuckles]

394
00:19:44.789 --> 00:19:45.832
What did he look like?

395
00:19:45.915 --> 00:19:48.126
[smacks lips]
I didn't get a good look at him.

396
00:19:48.835 --> 00:19:51.087
The only thing I could really see
were his… his boots.

397
00:19:51.170 --> 00:19:52.213
Boots?

398
00:19:52.297 --> 00:19:54.340
[stammers] He was wearing
Trevor's Red Wings.

399
00:19:54.424 --> 00:19:56.092
I could tell
because of the mismatched laces.

400
00:19:56.175 --> 00:19:57.176
Mismatched laces.

401
00:19:58.761 --> 00:20:00.179
Right. right.

402
00:20:00.263 --> 00:20:02.140
You know who that was. don't you?

403
00:20:02.724 --> 00:20:04.475
- [stammers] No. I...
- [door opens]

404
00:20:04.559 --> 00:20:05.685
Hi.

405
00:20:05.768 --> 00:20:08.521
I'm sorry about this.
but don't fucking move.

406
00:20:08.605 --> 00:20:11.065
[tense music playing]

407
00:20:14.110 --> 00:20:16.779
- [elevator dings]
- Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.

408
00:20:18.364 --> 00:20:19.657
Hiya.

409
00:20:19.741 --> 00:20:22.827
[chuckles. sighs]

410
00:20:24.370 --> 00:20:26.581
- Gym time. Nice.
- [chuckles]

411
00:20:29.626 --> 00:20:31.920
You're in admissions at Yale. right?

412
00:20:32.795 --> 00:20:34.839
- Yes. how did you...
- Go. Bulldogs.

413
00:20:34.923 --> 00:20:37.300
- [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

414
00:20:38.009 --> 00:20:41.429
Yeah. I don't know.
it's a son of a friend. really good kid.

415
00:20:41.512 --> 00:20:43.765
He. uh. just got rejected there.

416
00:20:44.349 --> 00:20:46.059
Oh. sorry.

417
00:20:46.768 --> 00:20:48.561
Have to make a lot of tough decisions

418
00:20:48.645 --> 00:20:50.230
and there's a whole bunch of us
in admissions. so…

419
00:20:50.313 --> 00:20:53.691
Yeah. but you're the only one
embezzling from the school. Joyce.

420
00:20:55.610 --> 00:20:59.113
- Whoa. Microsoft is tanking.
- [scoffs]

421
00:20:59.197 --> 00:21:01.533
Embezzling? That is ridiculous.

422
00:21:01.616 --> 00:21:05.036
[chuckles] They always say ridiculous.

423
00:21:05.828 --> 00:21:09.332
And yet. documents.

424
00:21:10.959 --> 00:21:12.585
Your brokerage account.

425
00:21:14.128 --> 00:21:17.048
Hey. you took a shot.
You know. no judgments from me.

426
00:21:17.131 --> 00:21:20.218
You were good at the stealing.
not so much at the hiding.

427
00:21:20.802 --> 00:21:27.183
But there is a way out
if you do a favor for a friend of mine.

428
00:21:28.476 --> 00:21:32.981
If you offer this young man…

429
00:21:33.731 --> 00:21:35.149
See his name?

430
00:21:36.109 --> 00:21:38.736
- I'm going to need a yes. Joyce.
- Yes.

431
00:21:38.820 --> 00:21:42.532
Yeah. if you offer him a place
in the upcoming freshman class.

432
00:21:42.615 --> 00:21:43.783
you won't go to jail.

433
00:21:45.869 --> 00:21:46.995
Oof!

434
00:21:47.078 --> 00:21:50.206
Looks like you've got
another really tough decision.

435
00:21:50.790 --> 00:21:52.500
[elevator chimes]

436
00:21:53.084 --> 00:21:55.461
Oh. This is me.

437
00:21:58.256 --> 00:21:59.465
Admit the kid.

438
00:22:04.971 --> 00:22:05.972
[sighs]

439
00:22:36.461 --> 00:22:38.922
- Ash. what are you doing?
- Please just let me go home…

440
00:22:39.005 --> 00:22:41.424
Just shut up or I shoot.
Do you understand?

441
00:22:41.507 --> 00:22:42.592
[breathes shakily]

442
00:22:42.675 --> 00:22:45.053
- You know who she's talking about?
- Obviously I know.

443
00:22:45.136 --> 00:22:46.804
I told you it was probably him.

444
00:22:46.888 --> 00:22:49.390
Trev warned us that if he ever found out

445
00:22:49.474 --> 00:22:51.267
that we were scamming people
behind his back.

446
00:22:51.351 --> 00:22:53.603
- it would be bad.
- Okay. you're right. You're always right.

447
00:22:53.686 --> 00:22:54.938
He's-He's gonna come for us too.

448
00:22:55.021 --> 00:22:57.857
- What do we do?
- I have an idea.

449
00:22:57.941 --> 00:22:59.150
Do you trust me?

450
00:22:59.234 --> 00:23:00.777
[panting] Yeah.

451
00:23:10.745 --> 00:23:11.829
[Dennis sighs]

452
00:23:13.915 --> 00:23:15.750
Hey. Bri-dog.

453
00:23:16.501 --> 00:23:20.004
Listen. good news. my man.
I did that favor for Cecilia.

454
00:23:20.088 --> 00:23:22.423
so. uh. should be good to go.

455
00:23:23.174 --> 00:23:25.510
All right. I will catch you later. my man.

456
00:23:28.054 --> 00:23:29.347
Bri-dog.

457
00:23:30.139 --> 00:23:32.392
- Kill myself.
- [phone buzzing]

458
00:23:37.730 --> 00:23:38.731
Hello.

459
00:23:38.815 --> 00:23:41.818
[distorted] <i>I have someone here
who witnessed you commit murder.</i>

460
00:23:41.901 --> 00:23:45.780
They can prove it was you.
but I've got them nice and secure.

461
00:23:45.864 --> 00:23:48.783
and I can give them to you for a price.

462
00:23:50.243 --> 00:23:51.494
[Dennis] <i>Okay.</i>

463
00:23:51.578 --> 00:23:55.039
How about go fuck yourself?

464
00:23:57.458 --> 00:23:59.127
If you don't pay.

465
00:23:59.210 --> 00:24:01.713
I'm going to drop them off
at the nearest police station

466
00:24:01.796 --> 00:24:05.425
with this phone number and your name.
and then you can go fuck yourself.

467
00:24:07.510 --> 00:24:08.511
How much?

468
00:24:09.721 --> 00:24:11.097
<i>Thirty thousand dollars.</i>

469
00:24:12.724 --> 00:24:13.725
[chuckles]

470
00:24:15.977 --> 00:24:16.978
Twenty.

471
00:24:18.396 --> 00:24:20.982
Half now and then I send the address.

472
00:24:21.065 --> 00:24:22.442
[whimpers]

473
00:24:22.525 --> 00:24:24.027
I'll text you where to send payment.

474
00:24:29.115 --> 00:24:31.409
You literally don't have to do this
because I...

475
00:24:31.492 --> 00:24:33.161
Shut the fucking mouth.

476
00:24:33.828 --> 00:24:35.955
[Sky] Are you crazy?
What are you thinking? What are you…

